<p><a name="Literature" id="Literature"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Movable_type&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Literature">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Literature</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Nesbitt, Alexander <i>The History and Technique of Lettering</i> (c) 1957, <a href="/wiki/Dover_Publications" title="Dover Publications">Dover Publications, Inc.</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486402819" class="internal">ISBN 0486402819</a> , Library of Congress Catalogue Card Number: 57-13116. The Dover edition is an abridged and corrected republication of the work originally published in 1950 by Prentice-Hall, Inc. under the title <i>Lettering: The History and Technique of Lettering as Design</i>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>The classic manual of hand-press technology is</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMoxon">Moxon, Joseph (1683–84), <i>Mechanick Exercises on the Whole Art of Printing</i> (ed. Herbert Davies &amp; Harry Carter. New York: Dover Publications, 1962, reprint ed.)</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mechanick+Exercises+on+the+Whole+Art+of+Printing&amp;rft.aulast=Moxon&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft.au=Moxon%2C+Joseph&amp;rft.date=1683%E2%80%9384&amp;rft.edition=ed.+Herbert+Davies+%26+Harry+Carter.+New+York%3A+Dover+Publications%2C+1962%2C+reprint&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Movable_type"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></dd>
</dl>
